The paper deals with the minimum distance of codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also discusses expander codes, which are a type of graph-based code and therefore could fall under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions low-density parity-check (LDPC) codes, which are commonly used in communication systems and therefore could fall under the category of computer communications (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the use of Reed-Solomon codes, which are commonly used in error correction and could fall under the category of signal processing (cs.SI) or networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
